<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-07-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-07-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="385" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d385">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Ryan</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Blaine</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-07-27"><hi rend="italic">July</hi> 27, 1890</date>.
                            (Received July 29.)</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Ryan reports, in reply to instructions regarding inviolability of
                        correspondence, that Salvador seems responsible, and that he has demanded of
                        her special agent in Mexico that the rights of the United States be
                        guarantied.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>